programme.title: Muster Dogs
programme.desc: In a high-stakes showdown between Team Collie and Team Kelpie, our six participants and their pups step through the five-month assessment tasks. They grapple with challenges and personal bonds.

programme.title: Troy
programme.desc: It is the year 1250 BC, during the late Bronze Age. Two emerging nations begin to clash after Paris, the Trojan prince, convinces Helen, Queen of Sparta, to leave her husband Menelaus, and sail with him back to Troy. After Menelaus finds out that his wife was taken by the Trojans, he asks his brother Agamemnon to help him get her back. Agamemnon sees this as an opportunity for power. So they set off for Troy with 1000 ships holding 50,000 Greeks. With the help of Achilles, the Greeks are able to fight the never-before-defeated Trojans, but they come to a stop by Hector, Prince of Troy.

programme.title: Repo Men
programme.desc: Supplying sophisticated and hugely expensive artificial organs to those in need, multinational company The Union has a virtual monopoly on life and death. Unfortunately, for those who cant keep up the repayments, the firms repo men are despatched to reclaim company property - no matter the consequences for the customer. After suffering a heart attack on the job, top repo man Remy wakes to find the company have fitted him with the latest heart replacement, along with a sizeable debt repayment. Unable to make the payments, and rapidly losing his taste for the job, Remy goes on the run, teaming up with his former wife, Beth, who is also fleeing the system.

programme.title: F9: The Fast Saga
programme.desc: The true meaning of family gets tested like never before as Dom Toretto takes the team on a worldwide ride with high-stakes action, old friends and a surprising new foe.

programme.title: Skyscraper
programme.desc: Former FBI Hostage Rescue Team leader and U.S. war veteran Will Sawyer now assesses security for skyscrapers. On assignment in Hong Kong he finds the tallest, safest building in the world, The Pearl, suddenly ablaze, and hes been framed for it. A wanted man on the run, Will must find those responsible, clear his name and somehow rescue his family who is trapped inside the building above the fire line.

programme.title: Doom
programme.desc: A frantic call for help from a remote research station on Mars sends a team of mercenary Marines into action. The team descends into the Olduvai Research Station, where they find a legion of nightmarish creatures, lurking in the darkness, killing at will. Once there, the Marines must use an arsenal of firepower to carry out their mission: nothing gets out alive.

programme.title: Punisher: War Zone
programme.desc: The Punisher is around and trouble begins when he accidentally kills an undercover FBI agent while raiding the warehouse of Mafia warlord Billy the Face, prompting a crisis of conscience in the vigilante. Billy is then fed through a glass recycling machine, creating one of the Punishers greatest comic book enemies, Jigsaw. The unfortunate agent had stashed away all of Jigsaws racketeering money, and the bad guy decides to lean on the dead mans widow and daughter to recover it, which doesnt go down at all with The Punisher.

programme.title: The Dark Tower
programme.desc: Roland and the Man in Black share an ancient vendetta: they must fight to the death in an epic battle over the fate of the universe. The last Gunslinger, Roland Deschain has been locked in an eternal battle with Walter ODim, also known as the Man in Black, determined to prevent him from toppling the Dark Tower, which holds the universe together. With the fate of the worlds at stake, good and evil will collide in the ultimate battle as only Roland can defend the Tower from the Man in Black.

programme.title: Jack Reacher: Never Go Back
programme.desc: When an Army Major is framed for treason, Reacher discovers shes the target of a massive government conspiracy and risks everything to take down the corrupt organisation.

programme.title: Dragonheart: Vengeance
programme.desc: Lukas, a young farmer whose family is killed by savage raiders in the countryside, sets out on an epic quest for revenge, forming an unlikely trio with a majestic dragon and a swashbuckling, sword-fighting mercenary, Darius. Helena Bonham Carter voices Siveth, the ice breathing dragon who was once banished from the kingdom for failing to save the kings life. Compelled by the young mans cause, she emerges from hiding, using her fantastical powers on the trios adventurous journey which brings revelations and rewards beyond vengeance. Dragonheart: Vengeance is an exciting action-adventure filled with fantasy and humor that will thrill the entire family.

programme.title: The Meg
programme.desc: A deep-sea submersible part of an international undersea observation program has been attacked by a massive creature, previously thought to be extinct, and now lies disabled at the bottom of the deepest trench in the Pacific with its crew trapped inside. With time running out, expert deep sea rescue diver Jonas Taylor is recruited by a visionary Chinese oceanographer, against the wishes of his daughter Suyin, to save the crew and the ocean itself from this unstoppable threat: a pre-historic 75-foot-long shark known as the Megalodon. What no one could have imagined is that, years before, Taylor had encountered this same terrifying creature. Now, teamed with Suyin, he must confront his fears and risk his own life to save everyone trapped below bringing him face to face once more with the greatest and largest predator of all time.

programme.title: Machete
programme.desc: Left for dead after clashing with notorious Mexican drug kingpin Torrez, Machete has escaped to Texas, looking to disappear and forget his tragic past. What he finds is a web of corruption and deceit that leaves a bullet in a senator and Machete a wanted man. Machete sets out to clear his name and expose a deep conspiracy. But standing in his way are a ruthless businessman with an endless payroll of killers, a twisted border vigilante leading a small army, and a beautiful Immigration officer torn between enforcing the law and doing what is right.

programme.title: Venom
programme.desc: Eddie Brock is a broken man after he loses everything including his job and fiancee. Just when his life is at its lowest, he becomes host to an alien symbiote which results in extraordinary superpowers - transforming him into Venom. Will these powers be enough for this new lethal protector to defeat great evil forces, especially against the far stronger and more weaponized symbiote rival, Riot?

programme.title: The Prestige
programme.desc: The mysterious story of two magicians whose intense rivalry leads them on a lifelong battle for supremacy full of obsession, deceit, and jealousy with dangerous and deadly consequences. From the time that they first met as young magicians on the rise, Robert Anglier and Alfred Borden were competitors. However, their friendly competition evolves into a bitter rivalry making them fierce enemies-for-life and consequently jeopardising the lives of everyone around them. Full of twists and turns, this film is set against the backdrop of turn-of-the-century London.

programme.title: Doomsday
programme.desc: This futuristic action thriller relates the details of the spread of the highly infectious Reaper virus, which resulted in the erection of a 30-foot-high wall of reinforced steel to block off the top area of the United Kingdom. More than 25 years later, with a new strain of the virus now threatening an overcrowded London, Major Eden Sinclair is sent to the infected zone to find a cure. Upon arrival, she finds herself confronted by a population gone wild, descended into utter savagery and cannibalism.

programme.title: Mission: Impossible II
programme.desc: Special Agent Ethan Hunt teams up with the villains ex-girlfriend to destroy an international conspiracy to sell a deadly virus to the highest bidder.

programme.title: Bloodshot
programme.desc: Based on the Valiant Comics series, Bloodshot, an ex-killer for the mob and slain soldier, is re-animated with superpowers.

programme.title: The Great Wall
programme.desc: Set in ancient China, a mercenary travels east in search of gunpowder and discovers the mighty Great Wall and the terrible secret behind why it was built.

programme.title: White House Down
programme.desc: Capitol Policeman John Cale has just been denied his dream job with the Secret Service of protecting President James Sawyer. Not wanting to let down his little girl with the news, he takes her on a tour of the White House, during which the complex is overtaken by a heavily armed paramilitary group. Now, with the nations government falling into chaos and time running out, its up to Cale to save the president, his daughter, and the country.

programme.title: Wonder Woman (2017)
programme.desc: Before she was Wonder Woman, she was Diana, princess of the Amazons, trained to be an unconquerable warrior. Raised on a sheltered island paradise, when an American pilot crashes on their shores and tells of a massive conflict raging in the outside world, Diana leaves her home, convinced she can stop the threat. Fighting alongside man in a war to end all wars, Diana will discover her full powers and her true destiny.

programme.title: Escape Room: Tournament of Champions
programme.desc: Six people unwittingly find themselves locked in another series of escape rooms, slowly uncovering what they have in common to survive. Joining forces with two of the original survivors, they soon discover theyve all played the game before.

programme.title: Fast and Furious 5
programme.desc: Dom Toretto and Brian OConner lead a reunion of returning all-stars from every chapter of the explosive franchise built on speed to assemble for a high-stakes race that places an unlikely alliance of cops and racers in from Rio de Janeiro. The team must also defeat a corrupt businessman who wants them all dead. A dogged federal agent whose strike team tears through South America in hot pursuit, but soon has a difficult time determining the good men from the bad.

programme.title: Interstellar
programme.desc: With our time on Earth coming to an end, a team of explorers undertakes the most important mission in human history: travelling beyond this galaxy to discover whether mankind has a future among the stars.

programme.title: Mission: Impossible
programme.desc: Theres a traitor in the heart of Americas most secret spy network, the Impossible Mission Force. He or she is trying to steal IMFs critical agent list which would give Americas enemies the names of every covert operative in the world. When a mission goes badly wrong, agent Ethan Hunt (Cruise) is suspected of being the turncoat and becomes a hunted man. With all the might of IMF now turned against him, Hunt must flush out the real traitor - even if that means stealing the secret list himself.

programme.title: Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom
programme.desc: When the abandoned islands dormant volcano begins roaring to life, Owen and Claire mount a campaign to rescue the remaining dinosaurs from this extinction-level event.

programme.title: The Accountant
programme.desc: Christian Wolff is a math savant with more affinity for numbers than people. Behind the cover of a small-town CPA office, he works as a freelance accountant for some of the worlds most dangerous criminal organisations. With the Treasury Departments Crime Enforcement Division, run by Ray King, starting to close in, Christian takes on a legitimate client: a state-of-the-art robotics company where an accounting clerk has discovered a discrepancy involving millions of dollars. But as Christian uncooks the books and gets closer to the truth, it is the body count that starts to rise.

programme.title: Robin Hood (2010)
programme.desc: Robin Hood, the legendary figure of 13th century England, who along with his band of marauders confront corruption in the local village of Nottingham and lead an uprising against the crown that will forever alter the balance of world power. Whether regarded as thief or hero, one man from humble beginnings will become an eternal symbol of freedom for his people.

programme.title: Troy
programme.desc: It is the year 1250 BC, during the late Bronze Age. Two emerging nations begin to clash after Paris, the Trojan prince, convinces Helen, Queen of Sparta, to leave her husband Menelaus, and sail with him back to Troy. After Menelaus finds out that his wife was taken by the Trojans, he asks his brother Agamemnon to help him get her back. Agamemnon sees this as an opportunity for power. So they set off for Troy with 1000 ships holding 50,000 Greeks. With the help of Achilles, the Greeks are able to fight the never-before-defeated Trojans, but they come to a stop by Hector, Prince of Troy.

programme.title: Repo Men
programme.desc: Supplying sophisticated and hugely expensive artificial organs to those in need, multinational company The Union has a virtual monopoly on life and death. Unfortunately, for those who cant keep up the repayments, the firms repo men are despatched to reclaim company property - no matter the consequences for the customer. After suffering a heart attack on the job, top repo man Remy wakes to find the company have fitted him with the latest heart replacement, along with a sizeable debt repayment. Unable to make the payments, and rapidly losing his taste for the job, Remy goes on the run, teaming up with his former wife, Beth, who is also fleeing the system.

programme.title: F9: The Fast Saga
programme.desc: The true meaning of family gets tested like never before as Dom Toretto takes the team on a worldwide ride with high-stakes action, old friends and a surprising new foe.

programme.title: Skyscraper
programme.desc: Former FBI Hostage Rescue Team leader and U.S. war veteran Will Sawyer now assesses security for skyscrapers. On assignment in Hong Kong he finds the tallest, safest building in the world, The Pearl, suddenly ablaze, and hes been framed for it. A wanted man on the run, Will must find those responsible, clear his name and somehow rescue his family who is trapped inside the building above the fire line.

programme.title: Doom
programme.desc: A frantic call for help from a remote research station on Mars sends a team of mercenary Marines into action. The team descends into the Olduvai Research Station, where they find a legion of nightmarish creatures, lurking in the darkness, killing at will. Once there, the Marines must use an arsenal of firepower to carry out their mission: nothing gets out alive.

programme.title: Punisher: War Zone
programme.desc: The Punisher is around and trouble begins when he accidentally kills an undercover FBI agent while raiding the warehouse of Mafia warlord Billy the Face, prompting a crisis of conscience in the vigilante. Billy is then fed through a glass recycling machine, creating one of the Punishers greatest comic book enemies, Jigsaw. The unfortunate agent had stashed away all of Jigsaws racketeering money, and the bad guy decides to lean on the dead mans widow and daughter to recover it, which doesnt go down at all with The Punisher.

programme.title: The Dark Tower
programme.desc: Roland and the Man in Black share an ancient vendetta: they must fight to the death in an epic battle over the fate of the universe. The last Gunslinger, Roland Deschain has been locked in an eternal battle with Walter ODim, also known as the Man in Black, determined to prevent him from toppling the Dark Tower, which holds the universe together. With the fate of the worlds at stake, good and evil will collide in the ultimate battle as only Roland can defend the Tower from the Man in Black.

programme.title: Jack Reacher: Never Go Back
programme.desc: When an Army Major is framed for treason, Reacher discovers shes the target of a massive government conspiracy and risks everything to take down the corrupt organisation.

programme.title: Dragonheart: Vengeance
programme.desc: Lukas, a young farmer whose family is killed by savage raiders in the countryside, sets out on an epic quest for revenge, forming an unlikely trio with a majestic dragon and a swashbuckling, sword-fighting mercenary, Darius. Helena Bonham Carter voices Siveth, the ice breathing dragon who was once banished from the kingdom for failing to save the kings life. Compelled by the young mans cause, she emerges from hiding, using her fantastical powers on the trios adventurous journey which brings revelations and rewards beyond vengeance. Dragonheart: Vengeance is an exciting action-adventure filled with fantasy and humor that will thrill the entire family.

programme.title: The Meg
programme.desc: A deep-sea submersible part of an international undersea observation program has been attacked by a massive creature, previously thought to be extinct, and now lies disabled at the bottom of the deepest trench in the Pacific with its crew trapped inside. With time running out, expert deep sea rescue diver Jonas Taylor is recruited by a visionary Chinese oceanographer, against the wishes of his daughter Suyin, to save the crew and the ocean itself from this unstoppable threat: a pre-historic 75-foot-long shark known as the Megalodon. What no one could have imagined is that, years before, Taylor had encountered this same terrifying creature. Now, teamed with Suyin, he must confront his fears and risk his own life to save everyone trapped below bringing him face to face once more with the greatest and largest predator of all time.

programme.title: Ned Kelly
programme.desc: You can kill a man but not a legend. Ned Kelly and his brother Dan, sons of an Irish pig thief exiled to the Australian penal colony in 1843, formed the core of the Kelly Gang (with two other men), an outlaw gang that roamed across Australia for over two wild years. Kelly was a clever bandit, making his own homemade armour, including steel chest plates and helmets, to stop bullets from stopping him. Kelly was first arrested at 16 for horse stealing, but he became an outlaw when he killed a police officer who was harassing his brother.

programme.title: An American Tail
programme.desc: Fievel the mouse travels from Russia to America with his family in the late 1800s to seek freedom from cat persecution.

programme.title: The Angry Birds Movie
programme.desc: In this hilarious animated adventure comedy, youll finally find out why the birds are so angry. In an island paradise populated entirely by happy, flightless birds - or almost entirely, Red, a bird with a temper problem, speedy Chuck, and the volatile Bomb have always been outsiders. But when the island is visited by mysterious green piggies, its up to these unlikely outcasts to figure out what the pigs are up to.

programme.title: The Boss Baby: Family Business
programme.desc: Boss Baby continues to navigate the cutthroat corporate jungle gym of Baby Corp, while angling to achieve the near-impossible: the work-life balance of a modern career baby.

programme.title: Jumanji
programme.desc: Young Alan Parrish sits down as a young boy to play a game with his friend, Sarah, and on a roll of the dice is mysteriously transported into the strange jungle realm of Jumanji. There he remains trapped for 26 years, until two newly orphaned children, Judy and Peter, playing in the attic of Alans childhood home, free the now-adult Alan from the games clutches. But to defeat Jumanjis encroaching powers, the three reluctant players must find the now-grown Sarah and band together as a makeshift family to finish the game - before it finishes them.

programme.title: Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle
programme.desc: In the brand new adventure Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle, the tables are turned as four teenagers are sucked into the world of Jumanji. When four high-school kids discover an old video game console with a game theyve never heard of Jumanji they are immediately drawn into the games jungle setting, literally becoming the avatars they chose: gamer Spencer becomes a brawny adventurer; football jock Fridge loses (in his words) the top two feet of his body and becomes an Einstein; popular girl Bethany becomes a middle-aged male professor; and wallflower Martha becomes a badass warrior. What they discover is that you dont just play Jumanji you must survive it. To beat the game and return to the real world, theyll have to go on the most dangerous adventure of their lives, discover what Alan Parrish left 20 years ago, and change the way they think about themselves or theyll be stuck in the game forever.

programme.title: Jumanji: The Next Level
programme.desc: The gang is back but the game has changed. They discover that nothing is as they expect, as they try to escape the worlds most dangerous game.

programme.title: Journey 2: The Mysterious Island
programme.desc: The journey begins when young adventurer Sean receives a coded distress signal from a mysterious island where no island should exist - a place of strange life forms, mountains of gold, deadly volcanoes, and more than one astonishing secret. Unable to stop him from going, Seans new stepfather joins the quest. Together with a helicopter pilot and his beautiful, strong-willed daughter, they set out to find the island, rescue its lone inhabitant and escape before seismic shock waves force the island under the sea and bury its treasures forever.

programme.title: Jurassic Park
programme.desc: Eccentric scientist John Hammond plans to open a theme park consisting of live dinosaurs, genetically engineered from DNA. Archaeologists Alan Grant and Ellie Sattler are invited to view the park, only to find themselves being hunted when the dinosaurs break free.

programme.title: The Pirates Who Dont Do Anything
programme.desc: Those vegie-eating boys are back. Three veggies serve as cabin boys at a pirate-themed dinner theatre, where they long to move from table service to the stage show, but their incompetence, laziness and cowardice get in the way. But when a princess drags them into the 17th century to rescue her brother, whos been kidnapped by a nefarious pirate with designs on her kingdom, they have to overcome their issues and become heroes.

programme.title: Penguins of Madagascar
programme.desc: Recruited from youngsters into the global spy game, four penguins are called into action by a mysterious espionage organisation in order to save the world from a villainous octopus.

programme.title: The Secret Garden (2020)
programme.desc: When Mary Lennoxs parents suddenly die, she is sent to live with her uncle, Archibald Craven, on his remote country estate deep in the Yorkshire moors. While exploring, she discovers a hidden magical garden.

programme.title: Matilda
programme.desc: A wonderful little girl who happens to be a genius, along with her understanding teacher, outwit the worst parents and the worst school principal imaginable.

programme.title: Smurfs: The Lost Village
programme.desc: A mysterious map sets Smurfette, and her best friends Brainy, Clumsy and Hefty, on an exciting and thrilling race through the Forbidden Forest, filled with magical creatures, to find a mysterious lost village before the evil wizard Gargamel does. Embarking on a roller-coaster journey full of action and danger, the Smurfs are on a course that leads to the discovery of the biggest secret in Smurf history.

programme.title: Tom and Jerry
programme.desc: A legendary rivalry re-emerges when Jerry moves into New York Citys finest hotel on the eve of the wedding of the century, forcing the desperate event planner to hire Tom to get rid of him. programme.title: Road to Riches
programme.desc: There are collectors and then theres Mick. Hes filled his large house with Star Wars memorabilia - every square inch of it. The trouble is Micks super tolerant wife has decided their newborn baby - appropriately named Leia after Princess Leia - needs some room too! Lucas and Mick pick out pieces that will fetch great money - including a full-size Jar Jar Binks model that needs restoring - before putting it all under the hammer at a specialty auction. Lucas hits the country roads to meet farmer George. Its been drought for too long, and farmer George decides he needs to cash up a few old items, and Lucas is the man to get the job done. Some old football caps of Georges great grandfather have been sitting around gathering dust, so he decides to let them go - and one of them is a mid 19th century English test cap! Meanwhile, Adrian has invited Lucas in to look at a piece given to him by his father that might be worth a fortune. Its a jacket reputedly worn by Jimi Hendrix!

programme.title: Road to Riches
programme.desc: Its always amazing what people collect - and Shaun is quite the collector! Among his Pacific artefacts and bizarre art pieces, he has a full size stuffed brown bear. Previously a football club mascot, Shaun picked it up cheap from a fire sale of office furniture and now wants to see if Lucas can give it a good home. Shaun also has a handful of paintings in his garage that he picked up at a garage sale - $50 for 50 paintings. One of these catch Lucas eye - and turns out to be a genuine Arthur Streeton watercolour. Lucas meets Ian, a collector-come-author who love Australian history, and hanging on his wall is an iconic Ned Kelly movie poster that if authenticated and found to be original could be worth thousands! Lucas is invited to the country to help close a mystery. A landlord tells him that one of his tenants has disappeared without a trace, leaving him to dispose of a house full of collectables!

programme.title: Batman Begins

programme.title: The Dark Knight
programme.desc: With the help of Lt. Jim Gordon and District Attorney Harvey Dent, Batman sets out to destroy organised crime in Gotham for good. The triumvirate proves effective, but soon find themselves prey to a rising criminal mastermind known as The Joker, who thrusts Gotham into anarchy and forces Batman closer to crossing the fine line between hero and vigilante.

programme.title: The Dark Knight Rises
programme.desc: It has been eight years since Batman vanished into the night, turning, in that instant, from hero to fugitive. Assuming the blame for the death of DA Harvey Dent, the Dark Knight sacrificed everything for what he and Commissioner Gordon both hoped was the greater good. For a time the lie worked, as criminal activity in Gotham City was crushed under the weight of the anti-crime Dent Act. Everything will change with the arrival of a cunning cat burglar with a mysterious agenda. Far more dangerous, however, is the emergence of Bane, a masked terrorist whose ruthless plans for Gotham drive Bruce out of his self-imposed exile. Even if he dons the cape and cowl again, Batman may be no match for Bane.

programme.title: Watchmen: Chapter I
programme.desc: In an alternate world, the murder of a government sponsored superhero draws his outlawed colleagues out of retirement, into a mystery that threatens their lives and the world itself.

programme.title: The Punisher
programme.desc: Undercover FBI agent Frank Castle (Thomas Jane) is crushed when his wife and children are killed after accidentally witnessing a mafia hit. With nothing left to lose or to live for, Castle becomes The Punisher a one-man judge, jury and executioner who declares open season on criminals throughout America. Based on the Marvel Comics character, the film also stars John Travolta, Laura Harring, Samantha Mathis and Rebecca Romijn.

programme.title: Punisher: War Zone
programme.desc: The Punisher is around and trouble begins when he accidentally kills an undercover FBI agent while raiding the warehouse of Mafia warlord Billy the Face, prompting a crisis of conscience in the vigilante. Billy is then fed through a glass recycling machine, creating one of the Punishers greatest comic book enemies, Jigsaw. The unfortunate agent had stashed away all of Jigsaws racketeering money, and the bad guy decides to lean on the dead mans widow and daughter to recover it, which doesnt go down at all with The Punisher.

programme.desc: Megamind is the most brilliant super-villain the world has ever known, and the least successful. Over the years he has tried to conquer Metro City in every imaginable way. Each attempt, a colossal failure thanks to the caped superhero known as Metro Man, until the day Megamind actually defeats him in the throes of one of his botched evil plans. Suddenly, the fate of Metro City is threatened when a new villain arrives and chaos runs rampant, leaving everyone to wonder: can the worlds biggest mind actually save the day?

programme.title: Man of Steel
programme.desc: A young boy learns that he has extraordinary powers and is not of this Earth. As a young man, he journeys to discover where he came from and what he was sent here to do. But the hero in him must emerge if he is to save the world from annihilation and become the symbol of hope for all mankind.

programme.title: Blade
programme.desc: Before Blades mother gave birth to him, she was bitten by a vampire, which made Blade immune to vampires. Now a vampire hunter, Blade, joined by vampire detective Hannibal King and Dracula-descendent Frank Drake, slay vampires.

programme.title: Morbius
programme.desc: Biochemist Dr Michael Morbius tries to cure himself of a rare blood disease, but he inadvertently infects himself with a form of vampirism instead.

programme.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (2014)
programme.desc: The city needs heroes. Darkness has settled over New York City as Shredder and his evil Foot Clan have an iron grip on everything from the police to the politicians. The future is grim until four unlikely outcast brothers rise from the sewers and discover their destiny as Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles. The Turtles must work with fearless reporter April ONeil and her wise-cracking cameraman Vern Fenwick to save the city and unravel Shredders diabolical plan.

programme.title: The Last Rifleman
programme.desc: World War II veteran Artie Crawford lives in Northern Ireland. After his wifes death, he decides to set off alone to France to attend the 75th anniversary of the D-Day landings.

programme.title: Ghostbusters: Afterlife
programme.desc: When a single mother and her two kids arrive in a small town, they begin to discover their connection to the original Ghostbusters and the secret legacy their grandfather left behind.

programme.title: Schindlers List
programme.desc: The incredible true story of the enigmatic and opportunistic businessman Oskar Schindler, who saved the lives of more than 1100 Jews during the Holocaust. This emotional film chronicles the trials and triumphs of one man who made a difference, and the tribulations of those who survived one of the darkest chapters in human history because of his actions.

programme.title: Skyscraper
programme.desc: Former FBI Hostage Rescue Team leader and U.S. war veteran Will Sawyer now assesses security for skyscrapers. On assignment in Hong Kong he finds the tallest, safest building in the world, The Pearl, suddenly ablaze, and hes been framed for it. A wanted man on the run, Will must find those responsible, clear his name and somehow rescue his family who is trapped inside the building above the fire line.

programme.title: Hypnotic
programme.desc: Determined to find his missing daughter, Austin detective, Danny Rourke instead finds himself spiraling down a rabbit hole while investigating a series of reality-bending bank robberies where he will ultimately call into question his most basic assumptions about everything and everyone in his world. Aided by Diana Cruz, an unnervingly gifted psychic, Rourke simultaneously pursues and is pursued by a lethal specter, the one man he believes holds the key to finding the missing girl only to discover more than he ever bargained for.

programme.title: Godzilla vs. Kong
programme.desc: Legends collide as Godzilla and Kong, the two most powerful forces of nature, clash on the big screen in a spectacular battle for the ages. As a squadron embarks on a perilous mission into fantastic uncharted terrain, unearthing clues to the Titans very origins and mankinds survival, a conspiracy threatens to wipe the creatures, both good and bad, from the face of the earth forever.

programme.title: Waterworld
programme.desc: Earth is covered with water and the human race struggles to survive on dilapidated boats and makeshift floating cities. A drifter becomes caught up in the struggle between the evil Deacon and a childs secret key to a wondrous place called "Dryland."

programme.title: Jack Reacher: Never Go Back
programme.desc: When an Army Major is framed for treason, Reacher discovers shes the target of a massive government conspiracy and risks everything to take down the corrupt organisation.

programme.title: Nobody
programme.desc: After failing to fight for his family during a robbery, an unassuming father calls on skills from his hidden past to become a lethal vigilante blazing a wild ride to revenge.

programme.title: The Meg
programme.desc: A deep-sea submersible part of an international undersea observation program has been attacked by a massive creature, previously thought to be extinct, and now lies disabled at the bottom of the deepest trench in the Pacific with its crew trapped inside. With time running out, expert deep sea rescue diver Jonas Taylor is recruited by a visionary Chinese oceanographer, against the wishes of his daughter Suyin, to save the crew and the ocean itself from this unstoppable threat: a pre-historic 75-foot-long shark known as the Megalodon. What no one could have imagined is that, years before, Taylor had encountered this same terrifying creature. Now, teamed with Suyin, he must confront his fears and risk his own life to save everyone trapped below bringing him face to face once more with the greatest and largest predator of all time.

programme.title: Harold and the Purple Crayon
programme.desc: Inside of his book, adventurous Harold can make anything come to life simply by drawing it. After he grows up and draws himself off the books pages and into the physical world, Harold finds he has a lot to learn about real life.

programme.title: Venom
programme.desc: Eddie Brock is a broken man after he loses everything including his job and fiancee. Just when his life is at its lowest, he becomes host to an alien symbiote which results in extraordinary superpowers - transforming him into Venom. Will these powers be enough for this new lethal protector to defeat great evil forces, especially against the far stronger and more weaponized symbiote rival, Riot?

programme.title: The Prestige
programme.desc: The mysterious story of two magicians whose intense rivalry leads them on a lifelong battle for supremacy full of obsession, deceit, and jealousy with dangerous and deadly consequences. From the time that they first met as young magicians on the rise, Robert Anglier and Alfred Borden were competitors. However, their friendly competition evolves into a bitter rivalry making them fierce enemies-for-life and consequently jeopardising the lives of everyone around them. Full of twists and turns, this film is set against the backdrop of turn-of-the-century London.

programme.title: Kung Fu Panda 4
programme.desc: After three death-defying adventures defeating world-class villains with his unmatched courage and mad martial arts skills, Po, the Dragon Warrior (Golden Globe nominee Jack Black), is called upon by destiny to give it a rest already. More specifically, hes tapped to become the Spiritual Leader of the Valley of Peace.

programme.title: Mission: Impossible II
programme.desc: Special Agent Ethan Hunt teams up with the villains ex-girlfriend to destroy an international conspiracy to sell a deadly virus to the highest bidder.

programme.title: Bloodshot
programme.desc: Based on the Valiant Comics series, Bloodshot, an ex-killer for the mob and slain soldier, is re-animated with superpowers.

programme.title: Beverly Hills Cop II
programme.desc: Axel Foley turns up the heat when the street-wise cop leads sidekick Judge Reinhold on the trail of a weapons kingpin and his leather-clad hit-lady.

programme.title: Talladega Nights: The Ballad of Ricky Bobby
programme.desc: NASCAR stock car racing sensation Ricky Bobby is a national hero because of his "win at all costs" approach. He and his loyal racing partner, childhood friend Cal Naughton Jr., are a fearless duo - "Shake" and "Bake" by their fans for their ability to finish so many races in the #1 and #2 positions, with Cal always in second place. When flamboyant French Formula One driver Jean Girard challenges "Shake" and "Bake" for the supremacy of NASCAR, Ricky Bobby must face his own demons and fight Girard for the right to be known as racings top driver.

programme.title: Wonder Woman (2017)
programme.desc: Before she was Wonder Woman, she was Diana, princess of the Amazons, trained to be an unconquerable warrior. Raised on a sheltered island paradise, when an American pilot crashes on their shores and tells of a massive conflict raging in the outside world, Diana leaves her home, convinced she can stop the threat. Fighting alongside man in a war to end all wars, Diana will discover her full powers and her true destiny.

programme.title: Pineapple Express
programme.desc: Seth Rogen and James Franco channel Cheech and Chong in this hilarious comedy where lazy stoner Dale Denton (Rogen) becomes the only witness to a murder by a crooked cop and the citys most dangerous drug lord. Denton immediately heads to dealer Saul Silvers place and now theyre up to their neck in all kinds of trouble and must run for their lives with the mobsters hot on their trail and out to silence them forever.

programme.title: Spider-Man: Homecoming
programme.desc: A young Peter Parker/Spider-Man begins to navigate his new-found identity as the web-slinging superhero. Thrilled by his experience with the Avengers, Peter returns home where he lives with his Aunt May, under the watchful eye of his new mentor, Tony Stark. Peter tries to fall back into his normal daily routine - distracted by thoughts of proving himself to be more than just your friendly neighbourhood Spider-Man. But when the Vulture emerges as a new villain, everything that Peter holds most important will be threatened.

programme.title: Interstellar
programme.desc: With our time on Earth coming to an end, a team of explorers undertakes the most important mission in human history: travelling beyond this galaxy to discover whether mankind has a future among the stars.

programme.title: Mission: Impossible
programme.desc: Theres a traitor in the heart of Americas most secret spy network, the Impossible Mission Force. He or she is trying to steal IMFs critical agent list which would give Americas enemies the names of every covert operative in the world. When a mission goes badly wrong, agent Ethan Hunt (Cruise) is suspected of being the turncoat and becomes a hunted man. With all the might of IMF now turned against him, Hunt must flush out the real traitor - even if that means stealing the secret list himself.

programme.title: Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom
programme.desc: When the abandoned islands dormant volcano begins roaring to life, Owen and Claire mount a campaign to rescue the remaining dinosaurs from this extinction-level event.

programme.title: The Accountant
programme.desc: Christian Wolff is a math savant with more affinity for numbers than people. Behind the cover of a small-town CPA office, he works as a freelance accountant for some of the worlds most dangerous criminal organisations. With the Treasury Departments Crime Enforcement Division, run by Ray King, starting to close in, Christian takes on a legitimate client: a state-of-the-art robotics company where an accounting clerk has discovered a discrepancy involving millions of dollars. But as Christian uncooks the books and gets closer to the truth, it is the body count that starts to rise.

programme.title: Transformers: Dark of the Moon
programme.desc: A mysterious event from Earths past threatens to ignite a war so big that the Transformers alone will not be able to save the planet. Sam Witwicky and the Autobots must fight against the darkness to defend our world from the Decepticons all-consuming evil.

programme.desc: PowerPoint Ministries started as a vision of Dr Jack Graham and his wife, Deb, 20 years ago. They believed that the power of God was evident in their growing church and that His Gospel message should be spread beyond the walls of that church to the world at large. They put their faith into action and purchased airtime on the Trinity Broadcasting Network. PowerPoint Ministries was then officially launched in April 1994. Over the past 19 years, PowerPoint Ministries has grown to an expansive network of local, national, and international television and radio broadcasts. In fact, PowerPoint can be seen or heard by a potential audience of millions of television viewers and radio listeners across the United States, the United Kingdom, Australia, South Africa, Iran, Russia, Israel and more. programme.title: Hour of Power
programme.desc: Since 1970 the Hour of Power has been reaching viewers from around the world. Originally founded by Dr Robert H Schuller, the program became the most-watched religious program in the world, reaching 17 million viewers. Now under the leadership of Bobby Schuller, Dr Schullers grandson. The congregation worships at Shepherds Grove Church in Garden Grove, CA. The program aims to provide spiritual principles and practices that can help people, as they become happy students of Jesus and live a life of meaning. To learn more about who they are in Christ through the process of formation, to belong to his family of believers and become a part of the community and to heal as they are loved and then love and help heal others through mission. Jesus Christ ushered in the Kingdom of God into our world through His death and resurrection. He invites everyone to be a part of this amazing movement by trusting and following Him. There is no fuller, richer life than the one that is lived in Christ.

programme.title: Drive Thru History: The Gospels

The team drives from the cities to the outback in an iconic Holden ute, unearthing stories from history and today of people whose lives have been changed by Jesus, and who have deeply influenced this nation. Explore the lands of the Bible and uncover a window into the ancient past. Sift through the archaeological data, travel down the pathways of the Bible lands and traverse through the passages of its ancient cities, trade routes, and caves and understand and appreciate the challenges of life faced by Christian forbearers, and learn how God used the historical and geographic setting of the Bible lands to refine and develop their faith. Those same real places and same real settings - when examined in the modern era - can likewise become a passage for developing greater faith and devotion for God.

programme.title: Amazing Grace
programme.desc: In 1972, Aretha Franklin, the undisputed Queen of Soul, recorded an album of gospel music at The New Temple Missionary Baptist Church in Los Angeles, before an ecstatic live audience. The result, Amazing Grace, went on to become one of the biggest albums of Aretha Franklins career and one of her most beloved works. But even as the album gained fans around the world, few realised that the inspirational sessions had not only been recorded, they had been filmed by a camera crew led by Oscar winning filmmaker Sydney Pollack. However, due to technical problems, the film has never been seen. Until now. Music lovers wont want to miss this thrilling film, which is both an extraordinary look at a key moment in American musical and social history, and an invaluable record of one of Americas greatest artists doing what she did best.

programme.desc: Famed opera singer Maria Callas retreats to Paris in the 1970s after a glamorous yet tumultuous life in the public eye.

programme.title: Hypnotic
programme.desc: Determined to find his missing daughter, Austin detective, Danny Rourke instead finds himself spiraling down a rabbit hole while investigating a series of reality-bending bank robberies where he will ultimately call into question his most basic assumptions about everything and everyone in his world. Aided by Diana Cruz, an unnervingly gifted psychic, Rourke simultaneously pursues and is pursued by a lethal specter, the one man he believes holds the key to finding the missing girl only to discover more than he ever bargained for.

programme.title: Shoshana
programme.desc: Two British police officers Thomas Wilkin and Geoffrey Morton in their hunt for charismatic poet and Zionist freedom fighter Avraham Stern, who was plotting to evict British authorities.

programme.title: Christmas Eve in Millers Point
programme.desc: On Christmas Eve, a family gathers for what may be their last holiday in their ancestral home. As tensions rise, a teen sneaks out with friends to take over the wintry suburb for herself.

programme.title: The Best Christmas Pageant Ever
programme.desc: Nobody is ready for the mayhem and surprises that ensue when six of the worst youngsters disrupt the towns yearly Christmas performance.

programme.title: Thelma
programme.desc: When 93-year-old Thelma Post gets duped by a phone scammer pretending to be her grandson, she sets out on a treacherous quest across the city to reclaim what was taken from her.

programme.title: The Heist Before Christmas
programme.desc: A Christmas-hating boy meets two Santas in the woods, one of whom claims to have fallen from his sleigh, but he is more interested in the other man when he learns he is on the run for robbing a bank.

programme.title: The Color Purple
programme.desc: Torn apart from her sister Nettie and her children, Celie faces many hardships in her life, including an abusive husband simply called Mister. With the support of sultry singer Shug Avery and stand-her-ground stepdaughter Sofia, Celie ultimately finds extraordinary strength in the unbreakable bonds of a new kind of sisterhood.

programme.title: Bob Marley: One Love
programme.desc: Celebrate the life and music of an icon who inspired generations through his message of love, peace, and unity. In this powerful and uplifting film, discover Bob Marleys incredible story of overcoming adversity and the journey behind his revolutionary music that changed the world.

programme.title: Anora
programme.desc: Anora, a Brooklyn sex worker, marries an oligarchs son. But when the news reaches Russia, his parents rush to New York to have the marriage annulled, threatening her fairytale.

programme.title: Mean Girls (2024)
programme.desc: In a musical twist of the cult classic, new student Cady Heron is welcomed by the popular girls called "The Plastics". However, when Cady falls for queen bee Reginas ex-boyfriend, she finds herself in Reginas crosshairs. She must learn to stay true to herself while navigating the most cut throat jungle of all: high school.

programme.title: Wicked
programme.desc: In Oz, two clashing witches, Elphaba and Glinda, form an unlikely friendship. Elphaba, wrongly labeled wicked, seeks to expose the corrupt Wizard ruling the land.

programme.title: Wonka
programme.desc: Based on the extraordinary character at the center of Charlie and the Chocolate Factory, Wonka tells the wondrous story of how the worlds greatest inventor, magician and chocolate-maker became the beloved Willy Wonka we know today. A young Willy Wonka, chock-full of ideas and determined to change the world one delectable bite at a time - proving that the best things in life begin with a dream, and if youre lucky enough to meet Willy Wonka, anything is possible.

programme.title: Dune: Part Two
programme.desc: Dune: Part Two will explore the mythic journey of Paul Atreides as he unites with Chani and the Fremen while on a warpath of revenge against the conspirators who destroyed his family. Facing a choice between the love of his life and the fate of the known universe, he endeavors to prevent a terrible future only he can foresee.

programme.title: Ghostbusters: Frozen Empire
programme.desc: The Spenglers return to the New York City firehouse where the original Ghostbusters have taken ghost-busting to the next level. When the discovery of an ancient artefact unleashes an evil force, Ghostbusters new and old must unite to save the world.

programme.title: I Saw the TV Glow
programme.desc: A classmate introduces teenage Owen to a mysterious late-night TV show - a vision of a supernatural world beneath their own. Owens view of reality begins to crack.

programme.title: The Holdovers
programme.desc: A curmudgeonly instructor at a prep school is forced to remain on campus during Christmas break to babysit a handful of students with nowhere to go.

programme.title: Ezra

programme.title: The Caine Mutiny Court-Martial
programme.desc: A naval officer stands trial for mutiny after taking command from a ship captain he feels is acting in an unstable way, putting in danger both the ship and its crew.

programme.title: Cassino in Ischia
programme.desc: Nic Cassino goes to Italy to work with struggling Italian directors on the first-ever "Neo-Realist" action movie in an effort to revitalize his career.

programme.title: Sumotherhood
programme.desc: Two wannabe gangsters hold up a local bank, but when things dont go according to plan, a misunderstanding leads them into business with one of East Londons most notorious gangs.

programme.title: Firebrand
programme.desc: Katherine Parr, Henry VIIIs sixth wife, becomes regent while he battles abroad. When he returns sick and paranoid, she must fight for her survival.

programme.title: See No Evil
programme.desc: Single mum Laura Ackerson leaves for work one morning and never returns. With no leads, police turn to surveillance cameras to locate her. But the more footage they uncover, the more sinister the case becomes.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: In the dead of night on a lonely San Diego highway, firefighters find a charred body in a burned-out convertible. Shot twice in the head before being set ablaze, the victim is David Stevens, an amateur bodybuilder and Nebraska native. But just who would want to kill the man described by friends as a naive and easygoing "good ole boy"? The only clue for investigators, Stevens unkempt bed, reveals he had sex with a mystery woman hours before he was murdered. A voodoo priestess, a stripper, and an ex-con make the list of possible suspects. When the investigation stalls, the victims family hires their own private investigator. After a series of false leads, the bizarre case eventually goes cold - that is, until a woman makes a sensational confession, and a sordid tale of jealousy, sex, and cold-blooded murder is finally revealed.

programme.title: Murder at My Door
programme.desc: The story of a teenager named Margaret, who vanishes while in the care of her fathers family friends following his death.

programme.title: The Real Manhunter
programme.desc: Following ex-detective Colin Sutton, a former senior investigating officer with the Metropolitan Police, as he looks back at his most important cases and the investigations.

programme.title: When Missing Turns to Murder
programme.desc: British true crime documentary series using powerful and emotional testimony from families and friends when a missing persons enquiry turns into a murder investigation.

programme.title: The First 48
programme.desc: In Memphis, Sgt Bart Ragland must find out who shot and robbed a family man. In Tucson, Detective Jim Hanson hunts two suspects who allegedly gunned down a local high school student as he and his friends walked home from the mall.

programme.title: See No Evil
programme.desc: Michelle Mockbee goes to work early to get a jumpstart on payroll. Less than an hour later, shes murdered outside her office. Surveillance footage leads detectives to a closet full of dirty secrets.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Just outside Memphis, an affluent Tennessee community is stunned when, in the early morning hours, a gentle, much-loved McDonalds manager is brutally attacked and left for dead on the floor of the restaurant. In critical condition, shes rushed to the hospital, where she dies soon after. In a town that prides itself on obeying the speed limit, the local police force goes into overdrive. The crime scene yields few clues, and with no signs of forced entry, investigators conclude the victim knew her killer. With a staggering list of possible suspects, including hundreds of former employees, the victims husband, and an eccentric cat-loving couple, investigators are baffled, and the case eventually goes cold. But nearly two years later, an anonymous tip finally brings them face to face with Delma Ramseys killers.

programme.title: New Scotland Yard Files

programme.title: Australian Crime Stories
programme.desc: In 1969, Lucille Butterworth disappears from a bus stop in Tasmania. Seven years later, Geoffrey Charles Hunt confesses to the crime but despite damning evidence, police did not lay charges.

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Britain
programme.desc: Rachel Nickell was walking her dog on Wimbledon Common in 1992 when she became the victim of a vicious sexual assault and was stabbed over 40 times. Rachels two-year-old son, Alex, witnessed the attack. A passer-by found Rachels body, with Alex clinging to her side, repeatedly saying, "wake up mummy, wake up." A huge police investigation followed. The police didnt have many clues as to who carried out the murder, but they centred their investigation around one man, Colin Stagg. They began Operation Edzell, later described as a honey-trap, which involved an undercover female officer, Lizzie James, feigning a five-month relationship to try to coax the truth out of Stagg. By 1994 the police were convinced that they had enough evidence to send him to trial, but the judge at the Old Bailey threw the case out, saying it was the deceptive conduct of the grossest kind. Colin Stagg never completely escaped suspicion (even up to 15 years later), and in 2007 he received over 700,000 pounds in compensation. A fresh investigation uncovered new evidence and DNA tied serial killer Robert Napper to the crime.

programme.desc: A young couple on their way home from a night of birthday celebrations is gunned down while getting gas. With the killers long since vanished, detectives must rely on the grainy gas station video.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Its July 30, 1995, a scorching San Diego summer day. An unidentified young woman is discovered by the side of the road, naked, raped, strangled to death, and thrown out like a piece of trash. Police have few clues but waste little time investigating this haunting crime. DNA matches the victim to 18-year-old Shannon Conway, a troubled teenage runaway who was living out of a sleeping bag among the hippies and transients on San Diegos Ocean Beach. An initial sweep zeroes in on several suspects. Tim Arman, Shannons ex-boyfriend, is still bitter that she dumped him a year ago. Keith Martin, a hobo living out of his van, is known as an angry Vietnam vet with a grudge against women. Martins van, eerily splattered with blood, was spotted in the area on the night of the murder. Police become convinced Martin is the killer but they cant forensically link him to the crime. Then a third suspect enters the frame. The day before Shannon was killed, she jumped into a pickup truck with a man she had met minutes before. Despite three strong leads, the San Diego Homicide struggle to put all the pieces together. Until over a decade later, new advances in DNA testing help cold case investigators finally find Shannons killer and give closure to her heart-broken mother.

programme.title: Death Row Stories
programme.desc: On the night of June 5, 1983, the Ryen family of Chino Hills, California, were brutally murdered in their home; eight-year-old Josh Ryen was the sole survivor. Circumstantial evidence quickly pointed to Kevin Cooper, a convicted felon whod escaped from a nearby prison. Cooper was tried for four counts of murder and sentenced to death by the electric chair. Two decades later, appeals lawyers for Cooper discovered eyewitness accounts pointing to alternate suspects. San Bernadino police also covered up evidence pointing to Coopers innocence. But with his appeals denied, on February 10, 2004, Kevin Cooper was led to the death chamber while the US Supreme Court weighed a battle between the State of California and Coopers lawyers. Just hours before his execution, Cooper was granted a stay. Kevin Cooper remains on Californias death row and still maintains his innocence.

programme.title: Crime Investigation Australia
programme.sub-title: Date With A Serial Killer - Rodney Cameron
programme.desc: Rodney Francis Cameron was dubbed The Lonely Hearts Killer after he used a radio matchmaking program in 1990 to lure an unsuspecting woman to her death. Incredibly, he had only just been released from prison for two other killings in 1974. Camerons psychopathic tendencies appeared early in his life. At the age of 10 he tried to strangle a young girl. He then attempted to strangle two other women and moved into a life of alcohol and drug abuse, including experimenting with hallucinogenic chemicals. He also dabbled in Satanism.

programme.title: #textmewhenyougethome
programme.desc: #TextMeWhenYouGetHome became a viral, worldwide movement following the 2021 death of Sarah Everard. The slogan sparked awareness around the vulnerability women feel while out in public alone.

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Britain
programme.desc: On August 15, 1998, in the small village of Omagh in County Tyrone, Northern Ireland, a car bomb was detonated in the main shopping area. Twenty-nine people, including a pregnant woman and her two unborn babies, died as a result. Victims included children, Catholics and Protestants, and visitors from the Republic of Ireland and Spain. Three days after the attack, the Real IRA (RIRA) claimed responsibility. Although one man was charged and later convicted with the crime, he was released in 2005 due to evidence that the Gardai had tampered with his interview. To this day, nobody has been convicted for the crime. There have been allegations of a cover-up by the police force on both sides of the border, and of a lacklustre performance in the investigation by the then Royal Ulster Constabulary (now the Police Service of Northern Ireland). A civil case brought by members of the victims families claimed that Michael McKevitt, Liam Campbell, Colm Murphy and Seamus Daly were guilty of the bombings, and they were held liable for 1.6 million pounds of damages.

It was cold-blooded murder.

The only clue for investigators, Stevens unkempt bed, reveals he had sex with a mystery woman hours before he was murdered. A voodoo priestess, a stripper, and an ex-con make the list of possible suspects. When the investigation stalls, the victims family hires their own private investigator. After a series of false leads, the bizarre case eventually goes cold - that is, until a woman makes a sensational confession, and a sordid tale of jealousy, sex, and cold-blooded murder is finally revealed.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Just outside Memphis, an affluent Tennessee community is stunned when, in the early morning hours, a gentle, much-loved McDonalds manager is brutally attacked and left for dead on the floor of the restaurant. With a staggering list of possible suspects, including hundreds of former employees, the victims husband, and an eccentric cat-loving couple, investigators are baffled, and the case eventually goes cold. programme.title: Crimes That Shook Britain
programme.desc: Rachel Nickell was walking her dog on Wimbledon Common in 1992 when she became the victim of a vicious sexual assault and was stabbed over 40 times. Rachels two-year-old son, Alex, witnessed the attack. A passer-by found Rachels body, with Alex clinging to her side, repeatedly saying, "wake up mummy, wake up." A huge police investigation followed. The police didnt have many clues as to who carried out the murder, but they centred their investigation around one man, Colin Stagg. They began Operation Edzell, later described as a honey-trap, which involved an undercover female officer, Lizzie James, feigning a five-month relationship to try to coax the truth out of Stagg. By 1994 the police were convinced that they had enough evidence to send him to trial, but the judge at the Old Bailey threw the case out, saying it was the deceptive conduct of the grossest kind. Colin Stagg never completely escaped suspicion (even up to 15 years later), and in 2007 he received over 700,000 pounds in compensation. A fresh investigation uncovered new evidence and DNA tied serial killer Robert Napper to the crime.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: Its July 30, 1995, a scorching San Diego summer day. An unidentified young woman is discovered by the side of the road, naked, raped, strangled to death, and thrown out like a piece of trash. Police have few clues but waste little time investigating this haunting crime. DNA matches the victim to 18-year-old Shannon Conway, a troubled teenage runaway who was living out of a sleeping bag among the hippies and transients on San Diegos Ocean Beach. An initial sweep zeroes in on several suspects. Tim Arman, Shannons ex-boyfriend, is still bitter that she dumped him a year ago. Keith Martin, a hobo living out of his van, is known as an angry Vietnam vet with a grudge against women. Martins van, eerily splattered with blood, was spotted in the area on the night of the murder. Police become convinced Martin is the killer but they cant forensically link him to the crime. Then a third suspect enters the frame. The day before Shannon was killed, she jumped into a pickup truck with a man she had met minutes before. Despite three strong leads, the San Diego Homicide struggle to put all the pieces together. Until over a decade later, new advances in DNA testing help cold case investigators finally find Shannons killer and give closure to her heart-broken mother.

programme.title: Death Row Stories
programme.desc: On the night of June 5, 1983, the Ryen family of Chino Hills, California, were brutally murdered in their home; eight-year-old Josh Ryen was the sole survivor. Circumstantial evidence quickly pointed to Kevin Cooper, a convicted felon whod escaped from a nearby prison. Cooper was tried for four counts of murder and sentenced to death by the electric chair. Two decades later, appeals lawyers for Cooper discovered eyewitness accounts pointing to alternate suspects. San Bernadino police also covered up evidence pointing to Coopers innocence. But with his appeals denied, on February 10, 2004, Kevin Cooper was led to the death chamber while the US Supreme Court weighed a battle between the State of California and Coopers lawyers. Just hours before his execution, Cooper was granted a stay. Kevin Cooper remains on Californias death row and still maintains his innocence.

programme.title: Crime Investigation Australia
programme.sub-title: Date With A Serial Killer - Rodney Cameron
programme.desc: Rodney Francis Cameron was dubbed The Lonely Hearts Killer after he used a radio matchmaking program in 1990 to lure an unsuspecting woman to her death. Incredibly, he had only just been released from prison for two other killings in 1974. Camerons psychopathic tendencies appeared early in his life. At the age of 10 he tried to strangle a young girl. He then attempted to strangle two other women and moved into a life of alcohol and drug abuse, including experimenting with hallucinogenic chemicals. He also dabbled in Satanism.

programme.title: #textmewhenyougethome
programme.desc: #TextMeWhenYouGetHome became a viral, worldwide movement following the 2021 death of Sarah Everard. The slogan sparked awareness around the vulnerability women feel while out in public alone.

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Britain
programme.desc: On August 15, 1998, in the small village of Omagh in County Tyrone, Northern Ireland, a car bomb was detonated in the main shopping area. Twenty-nine people, including a pregnant woman and her two unborn babies, died as a result. Victims included children, Catholics and Protestants, and visitors from the Republic of Ireland and Spain. Three days after the attack, the Real IRA (RIRA) claimed responsibility. Although one man was charged and later convicted with the crime, he was released in 2005 due to evidence that the Gardai had tampered with his interview. To this day, nobody has been convicted for the crime. There have been allegations of a cover-up by the police force on both sides of the border, and of a lacklustre performance in the investigation by the then Royal Ulster Constabulary (now the Police Service of Northern Ireland). A civil case brought by members of the victims families claimed that Michael McKevitt, Liam Campbell, Colm Murphy and Seamus Daly were guilty of the bombings, and they were held liable for 1.6 million pounds of damages.

It was cold-blooded murder.

programme.title: Power and Glory of The Habsburgs
programme.desc: This series traces the historical sites tied to the illustrious House of Habsburg-Lorraine, offering a fresh perspective on an 800-year legacy that shaped Europes history.

programme.title: The Lancaster Bomber
programme.desc: The Lancaster Bomber tells the incredible story of how one of the most iconic aircraft in history was created and how, as Bomber Commands most destructive weapon, it went on to become instrumental in the defeat of Nazi Germany during the second world war. With contributions from military historians Alexandra Churchill, Dr Peter Johnston and James Holland, authors Leo McKinstry (Lancaster) and Mark Johnson (Pilots of the Caribbean), history enthusiast Arthur Williams and veteran Lancaster crewmembers, The Lancaster Bomber offers new angles on the aircrafts complex legacy, the brave multi-cultural aircrews who flew it and the celebrated, but controversial, Arthur Bomber Harris.

programme.title: American Dynasties: The Kennedys
programme.desc: Explore the Kennedy familys rise to power and how personal relationships within the Kennedy dynasty shaped national and global events from the Cold War to the Wall Street crash.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: On the night of February 28, 1943, a group of Norwegian raiders, fewer than a dozen men, set out on a covert mission to sabotage the Nazi-controlled Norsk Hydro factory in Telemark, Norway. Their target: the production cells of heavy water, a vital component in the development of Hitlers atomic bomb. Their bold mission successfully set back Hitlers atomic program by many months and allowed the Allies more time to build their own and win the race for the atomic bomb.

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: January 1, 1945: a damp, frigid morning in northeast Belgium. American airmen tend to the routine flight operations of Y-29, a forward air base within kilometres of the frontline. A light dusting of snow and ice clings to the pierced steel-plank runway and the pine trees that surround the air base. This will be the site of one of the greatest dogfights in history.

programme.title: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Both the Allies and the Nazis were always looking for a single knockout blow to end the war. Britains Sir Arthur Bomber Harris thought the answer might lie in strategic bombing. The idea was to blow the hell out of Germanys infrastructure and cities. This, he argued, would cripple the Nazis ability to wage a war and the ordinary people would soon lose the will to fight. But it led directly to the tragedy of Dresden, when Allied planes firebombed tens of thousands of ordinary Germans. The Germans believed that the knockout blow would come from their submarines. If they could only cut American supply lines to Britain across the Atlantic, then the Allied effort would collapse. So began a long game of cat-and-mouse between U-boats and British and American convoys. Conventional wisdom has recently changed as more and more secrets have been revealed, particularly in the last five to 10 years, as documents, files and photographs have been released. Code-breaking revelations and newly released government papers on both sides of the Atlantic have added a very insightful new dimension to the understanding of this, the worlds greatest ever conflict. With the very latest satellite-delivered terrain mapping and state-of-the-art graphics, this story can now be told with the very latest access to information which was not previously available.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters
programme.desc: Joachim Peiper and the SS marched US 285th Field Artillery Observation Battalion into a field near Malmedy in January, 1945, and shot them. The hunt to bring them to justice was messy and violent.

programme.title: Time Team
programme.desc: Castleford, a former Yorkshire mining town, conceals a big secret. Local people believe their town should appear on the list of great Roman cities alongside Colchester, Bath and St Albans. Its known more for its rugby than its history, but 2000 years ago, the great Roman highway of Ermine Street went through the centre and a huge fort dominated the town. Digging up the Co-op car park, the British Legion backyard and a local football pitch makes for a busy three days as Tony Robinson and the team help put Castleford on the map of Roman Britain.

programme.title: Secrets in the Ice
programme.desc: Mutilated bones are found in a Danish bog. A Russian island is explored. Strange patterns appear in Kazakhstan, and a unique fish colony is discovered in Antarcticas Weddell Sea.

programme.title: History Uncovered
programme.desc: An investigation into the most significant events of the 20th century from an entirely new perspective.

programme.title: Digging For Britain
programme.desc: In the West, one of the largest Roman buildings ever discovered in Britain, an Iron Age chariot is saved, and evidence is found of the transatlantic slave trade in Devon.

programme.title: Churchill
programme.desc: This definitive six-part series will explore every facet of Britains most legendary prime minster. Well reveal the secrets of his aristocratic upbringing, his formative years in the military, his rise to political power, his wartime leadership and his legacy. Well look at his biggest triumphs, most disastrous defeats and reflect on his lasting legacy.

programme.title: Hitler: Countdown to War
programme.desc: This episode reveals how Hitler manipulated and played games with the Czechs and with the western powers of Britain and France to achieve his ends.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: Among the first US Navy vessels to see action in the Pacific in WWII were the motor torpedo boats of PT Boat Squadron 3 in the Philippines during the Japanese invasion. And for the next three years, from Guadalcanal to the coasts of Japan, they ran reconnaissance and screening missions, landed raiding parties, and attacked enemy shore installations and supply barges. See how they lived up to the motto of John Paul Jones: "Give me a fast ship, for I intend to go in harms way."

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: In the aerial battleground of World War II, the P-51 Mustang proved itself to be the most famous war bird in history. Take a look at three of its most memorable battles. On November 2, 1944, Capt Donald Bryan leads a group of P-51s escorting B-24 bombers to their target deep inside of Germany when he runs into a huge gaggle of Me109s on the attack. On June 23, 1945, 2d Lt Bob Scamara takes off with a flight of Mustangs from Iwo Jima. His group is jumped by 17 Zeroes. On April 7, 1945, pilot Richard Candelaria becomes one of the first Americans to face the jet menace.

programme.title: Power and Glory of The Habsburgs
programme.desc: This series traces the historical sites tied to the illustrious House of Habsburg-Lorraine, offering a fresh perspective on an 800-year legacy that shaped Europes history.

programme.title: The Lancaster Bomber
programme.desc: The Lancaster Bomber tells the incredible story of how one of the most iconic aircraft in history was created and how, as Bomber Commands most destructive weapon, it went on to become instrumental in the defeat of Nazi Germany during the second world war. With contributions from military historians Alexandra Churchill, Dr Peter Johnston and James Holland, authors Leo McKinstry (Lancaster) and Mark Johnson (Pilots of the Caribbean), history enthusiast Arthur Williams and veteran Lancaster crewmembers, The Lancaster Bomber offers new angles on the aircrafts complex legacy, the brave multi-cultural aircrews who flew it and the celebrated, but controversial, Arthur Bomber Harris.

programme.title: American Dynasties: The Kennedys
programme.desc: Explore the Kennedy familys rise to power and how personal relationships within the Kennedy dynasty shaped national and global events from the Cold War to the Wall Street crash.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: On the night of February 28, 1943, a group of Norwegian raiders, fewer than a dozen men, set out on a covert mission to sabotage the Nazi-controlled Norsk Hydro factory in Telemark, Norway. Their target: the production cells of heavy water, a vital component in the development of Hitlers atomic bomb. Their bold mission successfully set back Hitlers atomic program by many months and allowed the Allies more time to build their own and win the race for the atomic bomb.

Code-breaking revelations and newly released government papers on both sides of the Atlantic have added a very insightful new dimension to the understanding of this, the worlds greatest ever conflict. With the very latest satellite-delivered terrain mapping and state-of-the-art graphics, this story can now be told with the very latest access to information which was not previously available.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters
programme.desc: The hunt for, Franz Stangl, the Nazi commandant of the Treblinka and Sobibor death camps in Poland. He was responsible for the extermination of around 900,000 men, women and children. At the end of the war, he escaped to Italy where he joined a rat-line organised by Vatican officials. From there, he disappeared.

programme.title: Time Team
programme.sub-title: Every Castle Needs A Lord, Henley In Arden
programme.desc: A castle reputedly as grand and important as Warwick once dominated the Midlands village of Henley-in-Arden. Now there is just a hill. An eccentric American millionaire has bought himself the title of Lord of the Manor, and hes desperate to know what his castle might have looked like in its Norman and medieval heydays. After three days, 10 trenches and one archery contest, Tony Robinson and the team believe they have the answer.

programme.title: Massive Engineering Mistakes
programme.desc: A construction crane comes crashing down onto a landmark New York bridge. In Sweden, Bruce Springsteen fans nearly bring a stadium to its knees. A massive fail takes out Bostons fresh water supply.

programme.title: American Historys Biggest Fibs
programme.desc: The American Revolution created not just a new independent nation but also numerous popular myths about its foundation that, in time, replaced the facts.

programme.title: The UnXplained
programme.desc: According to the Greek philosopher Plato, the lost continent of Atlantis was once home to an advanced civilization before it was destroyed in a cataclysm. But was Platos story merely a myth? Or did Atlantis really exist? For centuries, archaeologists have tried to uncover evidence to prove that this legend is true. Will Atlantis finally be re-discovered, perhaps by employing modern technology? Or will this lost civilization remain unexplained?

programme.title: Secrets in the Jungle
programme.desc: In Belize, researchers find a curious skeleton in a cave. An ancient city in Cambodia is revealed by a LiDar scan. In Australias far north, an old coin is unearthed on an island. Bolivian farmers discover something unusual hidden under the canopy.

programme.title: Time Team
programme.sub-title: Steptoe Et Filius, Isle Of Wight
programme.desc: A field near the east coast of the Isle of Wight. Scatterings of early pottery, some fine Roman metalwork, but as yet no signs of any buildings. The area is known for at least one grand Roman villa; could this be the site of a second?

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: Among the first US Navy vessels to see action in the Pacific in WWII were the motor torpedo boats of PT Boat Squadron 3 in the Philippines during the Japanese invasion. And for the next three years, from Guadalcanal to the coasts of Japan, they ran reconnaissance and screening missions, landed raiding parties, and attacked enemy shore installations and supply barges. See how they lived up to the motto of John Paul Jones: "Give me a fast ship, for I intend to go in harms way."

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: In the aerial battleground of World War II, the P-51 Mustang proved itself to be the most famous war bird in history. Take a look at three of its most memorable battles. On November 2, 1944, Capt Donald Bryan leads a group of P-51s escorting B-24 bombers to their target deep inside of Germany when he runs into a huge gaggle of Me109s on the attack. On June 23, 1945, 2d Lt Bob Scamara takes off with a flight of Mustangs from Iwo Jima. His group is jumped by 17 Zeroes. On April 7, 1945, pilot Richard Candelaria becomes one of the first Americans to face the jet menace.
